            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Trebuchet MS' fontsize='14' underline='true'>INSIGHTS</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Trebuchet MS' fontsize='10'>1. Customer Retention Drops Rapidly After Month 1 from (~0.46%) to (~0.34%) and continues declining gradually afterward. This indicates early churn is the biggest challenge.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Trebuchet MS' fontsize='10'>2. Long-Term Retention stabilizes at very low levels between 0.22% - 0.26% indicating long-term customer engagement.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Trebuchet MS' fontsize='10'>3. Overall Retention is Low (2%) indicating that most users do not stay active long term.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Trebuchet MS' fontsize='10'>4. 6-Month Retention is Extremely Low (0.14%) signalling an opportunity for life-cycle marketting engagement.</run>
            </formatted-text>
